textBeforeTable: 2011 District 1 By District During the application process, applicants self-select which King County Council District(s) their program or organization has impact in. Awardees whose project/impact show up in the charts below in multiple districts are indicated by an * next to the dollar amount. Non bond-service funds are awarded annually based on an application and panel review process. Applications are reviewed by staff for eligibility, accuracy, and completeness. 4Culture staff facilitate peer panel reviews. Panels are made up of administrators, practitioners and specialists in in the field, from throughout King County, with expertise in one or more disciplines. The panel selects and recommends the most highly qualified projects for funding based on published criteria. These recommendations are approved by a 4Culture volunteer advisory committee and the 4Culture Board. The total funding awards granted between 2008-2011 total $20,229,066 (including $2,208,938 for continued bond debt service for 7 regional facilities). Per a request by the King County Council, the charts below list 4Culture lodging tax funded awards for the years 2008-2011, sorted by Council District.
